 :tx/rationale "UNSOUNDNESS-LEDGER-7: F(S) monotonicity claim is false in practice. bilateral.rs module doc (line 15) claims 'F(S(t+1)) >= F(S(t)) (Monotonic convergence — Law L1)' — stated as a mathematical theorem. But Session 033 documents a drop from F(S)=0.67 to F(S)=0.58 due to 'Views H=0.5 placeholder vs batch methodology_score'. If F(S) can decrease during normal operation, the convergence guarantee is void. The claimed Lyapunov property requires ALL store operations to be monotonic wrt F(S), which is not true: (1) Adding a low-quality observation decreases the coverage ratio (covered/total increases total without increasing covered). (2) Adding a spec element without an implementation link decreases the coverage component. (3) The spec_count counter in MaterializedViews includes retracted specs (LEDGER-2), so the denominator grows even when specs are removed. The module doc language should be downgraded from 'Lyapunov function satisfying F(S(t+1)) >= F(S(t))' to 'heuristic convergence metric that generally increases as coherence improves but is not formally monotonic'. The spectral certificate and convergence rate bound (mixing time O(log(n)/g)) depend on this property and are therefore also aspirational, not guaranteed."
